Exercise 7 : Prompt Comparison
Objective:
Understand how clarity affects AI responses.
Task:
Evaluate two prompts.
Instruction:
Compare the prompts below and identify which one will give better output.
Prompt A:
“Write a product description.”
Prompt B:
“Write a 3-sentence product description for a budgeting app targeting young
professionals.”

Answer:
Prompt B
Explanation:
Prompt B will produce a better output because it provides clear instructions about:

Length (3 sentences)
Product type (budgeting app)
Target audience (young professionals)

This additional context helps the AI generate a more relevant, focused, and useful product description. In contrast, Prompt A is too vague and may result in a generic response.


Exercise 8: Technique Selection (Tricky)
Objective:
Test understanding of when to use each technique.
Task:
Select the correct prompt technique.
Instruction:
Scenario: You want AI to consistently follow the same writing style across multiple
outputs.
Choose the best technique and explain why.

Answer:
Correct Technique: Few-Shot Prompting
Reasoning:
Few-shot prompting is the best choice when you want the AI to consistently follow the same writing style across multiple outputs. By providing several examples of the desired style, tone, and format, the AI can identify patterns and replicate them more accurately in future responses.


